{"title_page": "Stagecoach West", "text_new": "{{for|the ABC television series from 1960/61|Stagecoach West (TV series)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox bus company\n| name             = Stagecoach West\n| logo             = \n| logo_size        = \n| image            = Stagecoach Swindon 22626.JPG\n| image_size       = \n| image_caption    = [[Alexander Dennis Enviro300]] bodied [[MAN Truck & Bus|MAN]] 18.240 in [[Oxford]] in 2008\n| company_slogan   = \n| parent           = [[Stagecoach Group]]\n| founded          = 1983\n| commenced        =\n| ceased           =\n| defunct          =\n| headquarters     = [[Gloucester]]\n| locale           = \n| service_area     = [[Gloucestershire]]<br>[[Bristol]]<br>[[Herefordshire]]<br>[[Wiltshire]]\n| service_type     = Bus & Coach services\n| alliance         = \n| routes           =over 80 \n| stops            = \n| destinations     = \n| hubs             = \n| stations         = \n| depots           = 6\n| fleet            = 391 (November 2019)\n| ridership        = <!-- Daily ridership --> \n| annual_ridership = 24.9 million (2018/19)<ref>https://www.stagecoachbus.com/media-library/files/west/annual-report-2019.pdf</ref>\n| operator         =Stagecoach UK Bus \n| ceo              = \n| leader_type      = Managing Director\n| leader           = Rupert Cox\n| website          = [https://www.stagecoachbus.com/about/west www.stagecoachbus.com]\n}}\n\n'''Stagecoach West''' is the trading name of Cheltenham & Gloucester Omnibus Company Limited, a bus operator providing services in [[Gloucestershire]], [[Bristol]], [[Wiltshire]] and [[Herefordshire]], in the west of England. The company is a subsidiary of [[Stagecoach Group]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Stagecoach in Swindon fleet no. 20956.JPG|thumb|[[Alexander PS type|Alexander PS]] bodied [[Volvo B10M]]]]\n[[File:Stagecoach in Sindon Fleet no. 33953.JPG|thumb|[[Alexander ALX200]] bodied [[Dennis Dart SLF]] in June 2012]]\n[[File:Stagecoach Cheltenham and Gloucester bus 15524 (VX09 NBG) Showbus rally 2009.jpg|thumb|[[Stagecoach Gold]] liveried [[Alexander Dennis Enviro400]] in September 2009]]\nIn 1983, [[Bristol Omnibus Company]]'s Gloucestershire-based operations were transferred to the Cheltenham & Gloucester Omnibus Company.<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01713578 Companies House extract company no 1713578] Cheltenham & Gloucester Omnibus Company Limited</ref> In 1985, the [[National Bus Company (UK)|National Bus Company]]'s Swindon and District operation was transferred to the same company. In 1986, all the assets were transferred to a new legal entity, Western Travel.\n\nIn 1986, Western Travel was privatised in a [[management buyout]] and in December 1987 purchased [[Stagecoach in Warwickshire|Midland Red South]].<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01556310 Companies House extract company no 1556310] Midland Red (South) Limited</ref> In 1993, Western Travel purchased Circle Line of Gloucester (primarily a school bus operator, who had started to compete on regular bus routes) before being sold to [[Stagecoach Group|Stagecoach]] in November 1993.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/stagecoach-acquires-western-1507086.html Stagecoach acquires Western] ''[[The Independent]]'' 27 November 1993</ref><ref>[http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml Midland Red Depots] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103190940/http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml |date=3 November 2013 }} MidlandRed.net</ref>\n\nIn 1988, [[National Welsh Omnibus Services]] was privatised in a [[management buyout]]. After being placed in receivership in January 1992, the Eastern Division was purchased by [[Stagecoach South Wales]]. After the Western Travel purchase, the [[Ross-on-Wye|Wye]] & [[Forest of Dean|Dean]] operations were transferred to Stagecoach West.{{Citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\nIn September 2018, the company took over the operation of eight routes in the Bristol and Bath areas from [[Wessex Bus]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20180721030647/http://www.wessexbus.com/news/ImportantChangesforWessexBus_694.html Important Changes for Wessex Bus] Wessex Bus 20 July 2018</ref><ref>[https://www.bristolpost.co.uk/news/bristol-news/wessex-bus-close-services-42-1806005 Wessex bus to close and services 42, 12 and 51 cancelled in Bristol and Bath] ''[[Bristol Post]]'' 20 July 2018</ref>\n\nOn 1 September 2019 Stagecoach West took over operation of the X5 ([[Weston-super-Mare]] to [[Cribbs Causeway]]) and Severn Express ([[Newport, Wales|Newport]] to Bristol) routes from [[First West of England]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstgroup.com/bristol-bath-and-west/news-and-service-updates/news/severn-express-and-x5-bus-routes-transfer-first|title=Severn Express and X5 bus routes to transfer from First Bus to Stagecoach|website=First Bus|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> In October 2019, Stagecoach West took over the [[South Gloucestershire Bus & Coach]] business with 53 vehicles.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20190924103723/https://www.stagecoach.com/media/news-releases/2019/2019-09-23a.aspx Britain's biggest bus and coach operator expanding in Bristol] Stagecoach 23 September 2019</ref>\n\n==Depots==\nStagecoach West operated six depots {{As of|2013||df=|lc=y}}:<ref name=AnnualReport>[http://www.stagecoachbus.com/uploads/stagecoachwestrpt_westreport.pdf Annual Report May 2012 - April 2013] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017133508/http://www.stagecoachbus.com/uploads/stagecoachwestrpt_westreport.pdf |date=17 October 2013 }} Stagecoach West</ref>\n*[[Bristol]] (Gypsy Patch Lane, Patchway)\n*[[Cheltenham]] (Lansdown Industrial Estate, Gloucester Road)\n*[[Gloucester]] (London Road)\n*[[Ross On Wye]] (Great Western Court)\n*[[Stroud]] (London Road)\n*[[Swindon]] (Cheney Manor Industrial Estate)\n\n==Routes==\nStagecoach West mainly operates services across [[Gloucestershire]], [[Bristol]], [[Herefordshire]], [[Wiltshire]] and into [[South Gloucestershire]], although some routes serve more distant destinations including [[Hereford]], [[Monmouth]], [[Oxford]] and [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]].\n\nThe local bus network is operated in two brands, Stagecoach livery & [[Stagecoach Gold]] with vehicles of a higher specification and generally providing more frequent, higher profile or interurban routes.\n\nRoutes operated as Stagecoach Gold services are: 10 [[Cheltenham]] to [[Tuffley|Lower Tuffley]], 55 [[Chippenham]] to [[Swindon]], 63 Forest Green to [[Gloucester]], 94 Cheltenham to Gloucester, 97/98 Cheltenham to Gloucester, S6 Swindon to [[Oxford]], X5 [[Cribbs Causeway]] to [[Weston-super-Mare|Weston Super Mare]] and Severn Express [[Bristol]] to [[Newport, Wales|Newport]].\n\nWhen Stagecoach West purchased [[South Gloucestershire Bus & Coach]] in November 2019, they took over operation of their existing local bus, Private Hire & [[Megabus (Europe)|Megabus]] work. This included the fleet but this has been replaced with newer vehicles sourced from across [[Stagecoach Group]].\n\n==Fleet==\n{{original research section|date=August 2019}}\n{{As of|2019|November|df=}}, the fleet consisted of around 400 vehicles (including training vehicles). Types include:\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro400|ADL Enviro 400 MMC]]s\n\n[[Scania N series|Scania N250UD]]s with ADL Enviro 400 MMC bodywork\n\n[[Scania N series|Scania N230UD]]s with ADL Enviro 400 bodywork\n\n[[Dennis Trident 2|ADL Trident]]s including one E400 bodied\n\n[[Volvo B10M]] (training)\n\n[[MAN Truck & Bus|MAN]]s with [[Alexander Dennis Enviro300|ADL Enviro 300]] bodywork\n\n[[MAN Truck & Bus|MANs]] with [[Alexander ALX300|ALX300]] bodywork (training)\n\n[[Optare Versa]] (training)\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro300|ADL Enviro 300]]s, one with Transbus International bodywork\n\n[[Scania K230UB]]s with ADL Enviro 300 bodywork\n\n[[Dennis Dart SLF]]s with [[Plaxton Pointer]] bodywork (one training)\n\nShort Wheel Base [[Dennis Dart|Dennis Dart SLF's]] with [[Alexander Dennis Enviro200|ADL Enviro 200]] bodywork\n\n[[Dennis Dart SLF]]s with ADL Enviro 200 bodywork\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro200|ADL Enviro 200]]s\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro200|ADL Enviro 200 MMCs]]\n\n[[Optare Solo]]s\n\n[[Volvo B10M]] with [[Plaxton Excalibur]] bodywork\n\n[[Volvo B10M]]s with [[Van Hool]] bodywork\n\n[[Van Hool|Van Hool Altano]] coaches\n\n[[Volvo B11R]]s with [[Plaxton Elite]] bodywork (Megabus)\n\n[[Scania K series|Scania K114]]<nowiki/>s with [[Van Hool|Van Hool Alizee]] bodywork (training)\n\n[[Scania K series|Scania K340<u>s</u>]] with [[Caetano Levante]] bodywork (Megabus)\n\n[[Scania K series|Scania K440s]] with [[Caetano Levante]] bodywork (Megabus)\n\n== See also ==\n\n*[[Buses in Bristol]]\n*[[Buses in Swindon]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website}}\n\n{{StagecoachGroup}}\n{{Bus services in South West England}}\n{{Transport in Gloucestershire}}\n\n[[Category:Stagecoach Group bus operators in England]]\n[[Category:Transport companies established in 1983]]\n[[Category:Transport in Bristol]]\n[[Category:Transport in Cheltenham]]\n[[Category:Transport in Gloucestershire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Herefordshire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Monmouthshire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Oxfordshire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Swindon]]\n[[Category:Transport in Wiltshire]]\n[[Category:1983 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Bus operators in Bristol]]\n[[Category:Bus operators in Herefordshire]]\n[[Category:Bus operators in Wiltshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the ABC television series from 1960/61|Stagecoach West (TV series)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox bus company\n| name             = Stagecoach West\n| logo             = \n| logo_size        = \n| image            = Stagecoach Swindon 22626.JPG\n| image_size       = \n| image_caption    = [[Alexander Dennis Enviro300]] bodied [[MAN Truck & Bus|MAN]] 18.240 in [[Oxford]] in 2008\n| company_slogan   = \n| parent           = [[Stagecoach Group]]\n| founded          = 1983\n| commenced        =\n| ceased           =\n| defunct          =\n| headquarters     = [[Gloucester]]\n| locale           = \n| service_area     = [[Gloucestershire]]<br>[[Bristol]]<br>[[Herefordshire]]<br>[[Wiltshire]]\n| service_type     = Bus & Coach services\n| alliance         = \n| routes           =over 80 \n| stops            = \n| destinations     = \n| hubs             = \n| stations         = \n| depots           = 6\n| fleet            = 391 (November 2019)\n| ridership        = <!-- Daily ridership --> \n| annual_ridership = 24.9 million (2018/19)<ref>https://www.stagecoachbus.com/media-library/files/west/annual-report-2019.pdf</ref>\n| operator         =Stagecoach UK Bus \n| ceo              = \n| leader_type      = Managing Director\n| leader           = Rupert Cox\n| website          = [https://www.stagecoachbus.com/about/west www.stagecoachbus.com]\n}}\n\n'''Stagecoach West''' is the trading name of Cheltenham & Gloucester Omnibus Company Limited, a bus operator providing services in [[Gloucestershire]], [[Bristol]], [[Wiltshire]] and [[Herefordshire]], in the west of England. The company is a subsidiary of [[Stagecoach Group]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Stagecoach in Swindon fleet no. 20956.JPG|thumb|[[Alexander PS type|Alexander PS]] bodied [[Volvo B10M]]]]\n[[File:Stagecoach in Sindon Fleet no. 33953.JPG|thumb|[[Alexander ALX200]] bodied [[Dennis Dart SLF]] in June 2012]]\n[[File:Stagecoach Cheltenham and Gloucester bus 15524 (VX09 NBG) Showbus rally 2009.jpg|thumb|[[Stagecoach Gold]] liveried [[Alexander Dennis Enviro400]] in September 2009]]\nIn 1983, [[Bristol Omnibus Company]]'s Gloucestershire-based operations were transferred to the Cheltenham & Gloucester Omnibus Company.<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01713578 Companies House extract company no 1713578] Cheltenham & Gloucester Omnibus Company Limited</ref> In 1985, the [[National Bus Company (UK)|National Bus Company]]'s Swindon and District operation was transferred to the same company. In 1986, all the assets were transferred to a new legal entity, Western Travel.\n\nIn 1986, Western Travel was privatised in a [[management buyout]] and in December 1987 purchased [[Stagecoach in Warwickshire|Midland Red South]].<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01556310 Companies House extract company no 1556310] Midland Red (South) Limited</ref> In 1993, Western Travel purchased Circle Line of Gloucester (primarily a school bus operator, who had started to compete on regular bus routes) before being sold to [[Stagecoach Group|Stagecoach]] in November 1993.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/stagecoach-acquires-western-1507086.html Stagecoach acquires Western] ''[[The Independent]]'' 27 November 1993</ref><ref>[http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml Midland Red Depots] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103190940/http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml |date=3 November 2013 }} MidlandRed.net</ref>\n\nIn 1988, [[National Welsh Omnibus Services]] was privatised in a [[management buyout]]. After being placed in receivership in January 1992, the Eastern Division was purchased by [[Stagecoach South Wales]]. After the Western Travel purchase, the [[Ross-on-Wye|Wye]] & [[Forest of Dean|Dean]] operations were transferred to Stagecoach West.{{Citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\nIn September 2018, the company took over the operation of eight routes in the Bristol and Bath areas from [[Wessex Bus]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20180721030647/http://www.wessexbus.com/news/ImportantChangesforWessexBus_694.html Important Changes for Wessex Bus] Wessex Bus 20 July 2018</ref><ref>[https://www.bristolpost.co.uk/news/bristol-news/wessex-bus-close-services-42-1806005 Wessex bus to close and services 42, 12 and 51 cancelled in Bristol and Bath] ''[[Bristol Post]]'' 20 July 2018</ref>\n\nOn 1 September 2019 Stagecoach West took over operation of the X5 ([[Weston-super-Mare]] to [[Cribbs Causeway]]) and Severn Express ([[Newport, Wales|Newport]] to Bristol) routes from [[First West of England]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstgroup.com/bristol-bath-and-west/news-and-service-updates/news/severn-express-and-x5-bus-routes-transfer-first|title=Severn Express and X5 bus routes to transfer from First Bus to Stagecoach|website=First Bus|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> In October 2019, Stagecoach West took over the [[South Gloucestershire Bus & Coach]] business with 53 vehicles.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20190924103723/https://www.stagecoach.com/media/news-releases/2019/2019-09-23a.aspx Britain's biggest bus and coach operator expanding in Bristol] Stagecoach 23 September 2019</ref>\n\n==Depots==\nStagecoach West operated six depots {{As of|2013||df=|lc=y}}:<ref name=AnnualReport>[http://www.stagecoachbus.com/uploads/stagecoachwestrpt_westreport.pdf Annual Report May 2012 - April 2013] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017133508/http://www.stagecoachbus.com/uploads/stagecoachwestrpt_westreport.pdf |date=17 October 2013 }} Stagecoach West</ref>\n*[[Bristol]] (Gypsy Patch Lane, Patchway)\n*[[Cheltenham]] (Lansdown Industrial Estate, Gloucester Road)\n*[[Gloucester]] (London Road)\n*[[Ross On Wye]] (Great Western Court)\n*[[Stroud]] (London Road)\n*[[Swindon]] (Cheney Manor Industrial Estate)\n\n==Routes==\nStagecoach West mainly operates services across [[Gloucestershire]], [[Bristol]], [[Herefordshire]], [[Wiltshire]] and into [[South Gloucestershire]], although some routes serve more distant destinations including [[Hereford]], [[Monmouth]], [[Oxford]] and [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]].\n\nThe local bus network is operated in two brands, Stagecoach livery & [[Stagecoach Gold]] with vehicles of a higher specification and generally providing more frequent, higher profile or interurban routes.\n\nRoutes operated as Stagecoach Gold services are: 10 [[Cheltenham]] to [[Tuffley|Lower Tuffley]], 55 [[Chippenham]] to [[Swindon]], 63 Forest Green to [[Gloucester]], 94 Cheltenham to Gloucester, 97/98 Cheltenham to Gloucester, S6 Swindon to [[Oxford]], X5 [[Cribbs Causeway]] to [[Weston-super-Mare|Weston Super Mare]] and Severn Express [[Bristol]] to [[Newport, Wales|Newport]].\n\nWhen Stagecoach West purchased [[South Gloucestershire Bus & Coach]] in November 2019, they took over operation of their existing local bus, Private Hire & [[Megabus (Europe)|Megabus]] work. This included the fleet but this has been replaced with newer vehicles sourced from across [[Stagecoach Group]].\n\n==Fleet==\n{{original research section|date=August 2019}}\n{{As of|2019|November|df=}}, the fleet consisted of around 400 vehicles (including training vehicles). Types include:\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro400|ADL Enviro 400 MMC]]s\n\n[[Scania N series|Scania N250UD]]s with ADL Enviro 400 MMC bodywork\n\n[[Scania N series|Scania N230UD]]s with ADL Enviro 400 bodywork\n\n[[Dennis Trident 2|ADL Trident]]s including one E400 bodied\n\n[[Volvo B10M]] (training)\n\n[[MAN Truck & Bus|MAN]]s with [[Alexander Dennis Enviro300|ADL Enviro 300]] bodywork\n\n[[MAN Truck & Bus|MANs]] with [[Alexander ALX300|ALX300]] bodywork (training)\n\n[[Optare Versa]] (training)\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro300|ADL Enviro 300]]s, one with Transbus International bodywork\n\n[[Scania K230UB]]s with ADL Enviro 300 bodywork\n\n[[Dennis Dart SLF]]s with [[Plaxton Pointer]] bodywork (one training)\n\nShort Wheel Base [[Dennis Dart|Dennis Dart SLF's]] with [[Alexander Dennis Enviro200|ADL Enviro 200]] bodywork\n\n[[Dennis Dart SLF]]s with ADL Enviro 200 bodywork\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro200|ADL Enviro 200]]s\n\n[[Alexander Dennis Enviro200|ADL Enviro 200 MMCs]]\n\n[[Optare Solo]]s\n\n[[Volvo B10M]] with [[Plaxton Excalibur]] bodywork\n\n[[Volvo B10M]]s with [[Van Hool]] bodywork\n\n[[Van Hool|Van Hool Altano]] coaches\n\n[[Volvo B11R]]s with [[Plaxton Elite]] bodywork (Megabus)\n\n[[Scania K series|Scania K114]]<nowiki/>s with [[Van Hool|Van Hool Alizee]] bodywork (training)\n\n[[Scania K series|Scania K340<u>s</u>]] with [[Caetano Levante]] bodywork (Megabus)\n\n[[Scania K series|Scania K440s]] with [[Caetano Levante]] bodywork (Megabus)\n\n== See also ==\n\n*[[Buses in Bristol]]\n*[[Buses in Swindon]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website}}\n\n{{StagecoachGroup}}\n{{Bus services in South West England}}\n{{Transport in Gloucestershire}}\n\n[[Category:Stagecoach Group bus operators in England]]\n[[Category:Transport companies established in 1983]]\n[[Category:Transport in Bristol]]\n[[Category:Transport in Cheltenham]]\n[[Category:Transport in Gloucestershire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Herefordshire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Monmouthshire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Oxfordshire]]\n[[Category:Transport in Swindon]]\n[[Category:Transport in Wiltshire]]\n[[Category:1983 establishments in England]]\n", "name_user": "YTRK", "label": "safe", "comment": "categories", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stagecoach_West"}
{"title_page": "Timeline of the 2019 Atlantic hurricane season", "text_new": "{{Update|date=September 2019}}\n\n{{Tropical cyclone timeline\n| Track=2019 Atlantic hurricane season summary map.png\n| First date= May 20, 2019\n| Last date= November 25, 2019\n| Average wind speed=1\n| Strongest system= Dorian\n| Winds=160\n| Pressure=910\n| Longest system= Dorian\n| Total days= 14.25\n| Five years= [[Timeline of the 2017 Atlantic hurricane season|2017]], [[Timeline of the 2018 Atlantic hurricane season|2018]], '''2019''', ''2020'', ''2021''\n| Year = 2019\n| Basin = Atl\n| Season = Atlantic hurricane season\n| Storm1= [[Hurricane Barry (2019)]]\n| Storm2= [[Hurricane Dorian]]\n| Storm3= [[Tropical Storm Fernand (2019)]]\n| Storm4= [[Hurricane Humberto (2019)]]\n| Storm5= [[Tropical Storm Imelda]]\n| Storm6= [[Hurricane Lorenzo (2019)]]\n| Storm7= [[Tropical Storm Nestor (2019)]]\n| Storm8= [[Tropical Storm Olga (2019)]]\n| Storm9=\n| Storm10=\n| Storm11=\n| Storm12=\n| Storm13 =\n| Storm14 = \n| Storm15 = \n| Storm16 =\n| Storm17 = \n| Storm18 = \n| Storm19 =\n| Storm20 =\n| Storm21 =\n| Storm22 =\n| Storm23 =\n| Storm24 =\n| Storm25 =\n}}\nThe [[2019 Atlantic hurricane season]] was an event in the annual [[tropical cyclone]] season in the North Hemisphere. The season officially began on June&nbsp;1, 2019 and ended on November&nbsp;30, 2019. These dates, adopted by convention, historically describe the period in each year when most systems form.<ref name=\"SeasonDates\">{{cite book|url=http://www.aoml.noaa.gov/hrd/tcfaq/tcfaqHED.html|title=Hurricane Research Division: Frequently Asked Questions|chapter=G: Tropical Cyclone Climatology|chapterurl=http://www.aoml.noaa.gov/hrd/tcfaq/tcfaqG.html|at=[http://www.aoml.noaa.gov/hrd/tcfaq/G1.html G1) When is hurricane season ?]|author1=Christopher W. Landsea|author2=Neal Dorst|author3=Erica Rule|work=[[Atlantic Oceanographic and Meteorological Laboratory]]|publisher=National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|date=June 2, 2011|accessdate=July 1, 2019}}</ref> However, systems can and do form outside these dates, such as Subtropical Storm Andrea, which formed on May&nbsp;20.\n\nThis timeline documents tropical cyclone formations, strengthening, weakening, [[Landfall (meteorology)|landfall]]s, [[Extratropical cyclone#Extratropical transition|extratropical transitions]], and dissipations during the season. It includes information that was not released throughout the season, meaning that data from post-storm reviews by the [[National Hurricane Center]], such as a storm that was not initially warned upon, has been included.\n\n== Timeline of events ==\n<center>\n<timeline>\nImageSize = width:800 height:215\nPlotArea  = top:10 bottom:80 right:20 left:20\nLegend    = columns:3 left:30 top:58 columnwidth:270\nAlignBars = early\n\nDateFormat = dd/mm/yyyy\nPeriod     = from:01/05/2019 till:31/12/2019\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nScaleMinor = grid:black unit:month increment:1 start:01/05/2019\n\nColors     =\n  id:canvas value:gray(0.88)\n  id:GP     value:red\n  id:TD     value:rgb(0.38,0.73,1)  legend:Tropical_Depression_=_\u226439_mph_(\u226462_km/h)\n  id:TS     value:rgb(0,0.98,0.96)  legend:Tropical_Storm_=_39\u201373_mph_(63\u2013117_km/h)\n  id:C1     value:rgb(1,1,0.80)     legend:Category_1_=_74\u201395_mph_(118\u2013153_km/h)\n  id:C2     value:rgb(1,0.91,0.46)  legend:Category_2_=_96\u2013110_mph_(154\u2013177_km/h)\n  id:C3     value:rgb(1,0.76,0.25)  legend:Category_3_=_111\u2013129_mph_(178\u2013208_km/h)\n  id:C4     value:rgb(1,0.56,0.13)  legend:Category_4_=_130\u2013156_mph_(209\u2013251_km/h)\n  id:C5     value:rgb(1,0.38,0.38)  legend:Category_5_=_\u2265157_mph_(\u2265252_km/h)\n\nBackgroundcolors = canvas:canvas\n\nBarData =\n  barset:Hurricane\n  bar:Month\n\nPlotData=\n\n  barset:Hurricane width:10 align:left fontsize:S shift:(4,-4) anchor:till\n  from:20/05/2019 till:21/05/2019 color:TS text:\"Andrea (SS)\"\n  from:11/07/2019 till:15/07/2019 color:C1 text:\"[[Hurricane Barry (2019)|Barry (C1)]]\"\n  from:22/07/2019 till:23/07/2019 color:TD text:\"Three (TD)\"\n  from:21/08/2019 till:24/08/2019 color:TS text:\"Chantal (TS)\"\n  from:24/08/2019 till:07/09/2019 color:C5 text:\"[[Hurricane Dorian|Dorian (C5)]]\"\n  from:26/08/2019 till:29/08/2019 color:TS text:\"Erin (TS)\"\n  from:03/09/2019 till:05/09/2019 color:TS text:\"[[Tropical Storm Fernand (2019)|Fernand (TS)]]\"\n  from:03/09/2019 till:05/09/2019 color:TS\n  barset:break\n  barset:skip\n  barset:skip\n  barset:skip\n  barset:skip\n  barset:skip\n  barset:skip\n  barset:skip\n  from:06/09/2019 till:10/09/2019 color:TS text:\"Gabrielle (TS)\"\n  from:13/09/2019 till:20/09/2019 color:C3 text:\"[[Hurricane Humberto (2019)|Humberto (C3)]]\"\n  barset:break\n  from:17/09/2019 till:25/09/2019 color:C2 text:\"Jerry (C2)\"\n  from:17/09/2019 till:19/09/2019 color:TS text:\"[[Tropical Storm Imelda|Imelda (TS)]]\"\n  from:22/09/2019 till:27/09/2019 color:TS text:\"Karen (TS)\"\n  from:23/09/2019 till:02/10/2019 color:C5 text:\"[[Hurricane Lorenzo (2019)|Lorenzo (C5)]]\"\n  from:11/10/2019 till:14/10/2019 color:TS text:\"Melissa (TS)\"\n  from:14/10/2019 till:16/10/2019 color:TD text:\"Fifteen (TD)\"\n  from:18/10/2019 till:19/10/2019 color:TS text:\"[[Tropical Storm Nestor (2019)|Nestor (TS)]]\"\n  from:25/10/2019 till:26/10/2019 color:TS text:\"[[Tropical Storm Olga (2019|Olga (TS)]]\"\n  from:25/10/2019 till:27/10/2019 color:C1 text:\"Pablo (C1)\"\n  barset:break\n  from:30/10/2019 till:01/11/2019 color:TS text:\"Rebekah (SS)\"\n  from:19/11/2019 till:25/11/2019 color:TS text:\"Sebastien (TS)\"\n\n  barset:Hurricane width:10 align:left fontsize:S shift:(4,-4) anchor:till\n  barset:break\n\n  bar:Month width:5 align:center fontsize:S shift:(0,-20) anchor:middle color:canvas\n  from:01/05/2019 till:31/05/2019 text:May\n  from:01/06/2019 till:30/06/2019 text:June\n  from:01/07/2019 till:31/07/2019 text:July\n  from:01/08/2019 till:31/08/2019 text:August\n  from:01/09/2019 till:30/