ww.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al01/al012019.public.005.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=May 21, 2019|accessdate=July 11, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n=== June ===\n'''June&nbsp;1'''\n* The 2019 Atlantic hurricane season officially begins.<ref name=\"SeasonDates\" />\n\n=== July ===\n'''July&nbsp;11'''\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (10:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Central Daylight Time|CDT]]) at {{Coord|27.8|-88.7|name=Tropical Storm Barry forms}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Barry forms about 95&nbsp;mi (150&nbsp;km) south-southeast of the mouth of the [[Mississippi River]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Jack Beven|title=Tropical Storm Barry Advisory Number 5|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al02/al022019.public.005.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=July 11, 2019|accessdate=July 11, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''July&nbsp;13'''\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (10:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Central Daylight Time|CDT]]) at {{Coord|29.6|-92.0|name=Tropical Storm Barry strengthens, peaks, and makes landfall}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Barry intensifies into a Category 1 hurricane, reaches peak intensity with 1-minute [[Maximum sustained wind|sustained wind]]s of 75&nbsp;mph (120&nbsp;km/h) and a minimum pressure of {{convert|993|mbar|inHg|abbr=on|sigfig=4}}, and makes its first landfall on [[Louisiana]] roughly 40&nbsp;mi (65&nbsp;km) south of [[Lafayette, Louisiana]] and 50&nbsp;mi (80&nbsp;km) west of [[Morgan City, Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Jack Beven|title=Hurricane Barry Advisory Number 13|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al02/al022019.public.013.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=July 13, 2019|accessdate=November 30, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 18:00&nbsp;UTC (1:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Central Daylight Time|CDT]]) at {{Coord|29.8|-92.1|name=Hurricane Barry weakens and makes landfall}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Barry weakens into a tropical storm and makes its second landfall on [[Louisiana]] roughly 5&nbsp;mi (10&nbsp;km) northeast of [[Intracoastal City, Louisiana]] and 30&nbsp;mi (50&nbsp;km) south-southwest of [[Lafayette, Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Jack Beven|title=Tropical Storm Barry Intermediate Advisory Number 13A|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al02/al022019.public_a.013.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=July 13, 2019|accessdate=November 30, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''July&nbsp;14'''\n* 21:00&nbsp;UTC (4:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Central Daylight Time|CDT]]) at {{Coord|32.8|-93.6|name=Tropical Storm Barry weakens}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Barry weakens into a tropical depression roughly 20&nbsp;mi (35&nbsp;km) north-northeast of [[Shreveport, Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Stacy Stewart|title=Tropical Depression Barry Advisory Number 18|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al02/al022019.public.018.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=July 14, 2019|accessdate=November 30, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''July&nbsp;22'''\n* 21:00&nbsp;UTC (5:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|24.6|-78.6|name=Tropical Depression Three forms}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Three forms from an area of low pressure roughly 120&nbsp;mi (195&nbsp;km) southeast of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Richard Pasch|title=Tropical Depression Three Public Advisory Number 1|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al03/al032019.public.001.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=July 22, 2019|accessdate=July 22, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''July&nbsp;23'''\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|29.0|-80.0|name=Tropical Depression Three dissipates}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Three degenerates into a remnant low roughly 60&nbsp;mi (100&nbsp;km) east-southeast of [[Daytona Beach, Florida]] and 100&nbsp;mi (160&nbsp;km) southeast of [[St. Augustine, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Daniel Brown|title=Remnants of Three Advisory Number 4|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al03/al032019.public.004.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=July 23, 2019|accessdate=November 30, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n=== August ===\n'''August&nbsp;21'''\n* 03:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]] August&nbsp;20) at {{Coord|40.2|-56.2|name=Tropical Storm Chantal forms}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Chantal forms about 485&nbsp;mi (780&nbsp;km) southeast of [[Halifax, Nova Scotia]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Stacy R. Stewart|title=Tropical Storm Chantal Advisory Number 5|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al04/al042019.public.001.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 20, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]]) at {{Coord|40.2|-51.6|name=Tropical Storm Chantal reaches peak}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Chantal reaches peak intensity with 1-minute [[Maximum sustained wind|sustained wind]]s of 40&nbsp;mph (65&nbsp;km/h) and a minimum pressure of {{convert|1009|mbar|inHg|abbr=on|sigfig=4}} roughly 455&nbsp;mi (730&nbsp;km) south of [[Cape Race, Newfoundland]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Richard J. Pasch|title=Tropical Storm Chantal Advisory Number 3|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al04/al042019.public.003.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 21, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;22'''\n* 03:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]] August&nbsp;21) at {{Coord|39.4|-47.7|name=Tropical Storm Chantal weakens}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Chantal weakens into a tropical depression about 580&nbsp;mi (935&nbsp;km) south-southeast of Cape Race, Newfoundland.<ref>{{cite report|author=Dave Roberts|title=Tropical Storm Chantal Advisory Number 5|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al04/al042019.public.005.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 21, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;24'''\n* 03:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]] August&nbsp;23) at {{Coord|35.6|-40.9|name=Tropical Depression Chantal dissipates}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Chantal degenerates into a remnant low about 785&nbsp;mi (1265&nbsp;km) west of the [[Azores]].<ref>{{cite report|author=David A. Zelinsky|title=Post-Tropical Cyclone Chantal Advisory Number 13|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al04/al042019.public.013.shtml?||publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 23, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]]) at {{Coord|10.4|-47.9|name=Tropical Depression Five forms}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Five forms roughly 805&nbsp;mi (1300&nbsp;km) east-southeast of [[Barbados]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Stacy R. Stewart|title=Tropical Depression Five Advisory Number 1|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public.001.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 24, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 21:00&nbsp;UTC (5:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]]) at {{Coord|10.7|-49.1|name=Tropical Depression Five strengthens}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Five strengthens into Tropical Storm Dorian roughly 725&nbsp;mi (1165&nbsp;km) east-southeast of Barbados.<ref>{{cite report|author=Stacy R. Stewart|title=Tropical Storm Dorian Advisory Number 2|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public.002.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 24, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;26'''\n* 21:00&nbsp;UTC (5:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|31.7|-72.5|name=Tropical Depression Six forms}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Six forms roughly 295&nbsp;mi (480&nbsp;km) southeast of [[Cape Hatteras, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Daniel Brown|title=Tropical Depression Six Advisory Number 1|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al06/al062019.public.001.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 26, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;28'''\n* 03:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] August&nbsp;27) at {{Coord|31.9|-72.1|name=Tropical Depression Six strengthens}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Six strengthens into Tropical Storm Erin roughly 430&nbsp;mi (690&nbsp;km) west of Bermuda.<ref>{{cite report|author1=Andrew S. Latto|author2=Richard J. Pasch|title=Tropical Storm Erin Advisory Number 6|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al06/al062019.public.006.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 27, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|33.6|-72.8|name=Tropical Storm Erin weakens}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Erin weakens into a tropical depression roughly 470&nbsp;mi (760&nbsp;km) west-northwest of Bermuda.<ref>{{cite report|author=Daniel Brown|title=Tropical Depression Erin Advisory Number 8|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al06/al062019.public.008.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 28, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 18:00&nbsp;UTC (2:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]]) at {{Coord|18.3|-65.0|name=Tropical Storm Dorian strengthens}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Storm Dorian intensifies into a Category 1 hurricane roughly 0&nbsp;mi (0&nbsp;km) west of [[Saint Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands|St. Thomas]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Lixion Avila|title=Hurricane Dorian Intermediate Advisory Number 17A|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public_a.017.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 28, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;29'''\n* 09:00&nbsp;UTC (5:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|31.9|-72.1|name=Tropical Depression Erin becomes extratropical}}&nbsp;\u2013 Tropical Depression Erin transitions into an extratropical cyclone roughly 430&nbsp;mi (690&nbsp;km) west of [[Bermuda]] and 300&nbsp;mi (485&nbsp;km) southeast of [[Cape Hatteras]], [[North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Jack Beven|title=Post-Tropical Cyclone Erin Advisory Number 11|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al06/al062019.public.011.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 29, 2019|accessdate=December 13, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;30'''\n* 03:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] August&nbsp;29) at {{Coord|23.3|-68.4|name=Hurricane Dorian strengthens to Category 2}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian intensifies into a Category 2 hurricane roughly 290&nbsp;mi (470&nbsp;km) east-northeast of the southeastern [[Bahamas]] and 580&nbsp;mi (930&nbsp;km) east of the northwestern [[Bahamas]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Eric Blake|title=Hurricane Dorian Intermediate Advisory Number 23|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public.023.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 30, 2019|accessdate=September 19, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 18:00&nbsp;UTC (2:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|24.8|-70.3|name=Hurricane Dorian strengthens to Category 3}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian intensifies into a major hurricane roughly 445&nbsp;mi (715&nbsp;km) east of the northwestern [[Bahamas]] and 625&nbsp;mi (1005&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Lixion Avila|title=Hurricane Dorian Intermediate Advisory Number 25A|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public_a.025.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 30, 2019|accessdate=September 19, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''August&nbsp;31'''\n* 00:30&nbsp;UTC (8:30&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] August&nbsp;29) at {{Coord|25.3|-71.0|name=Hurricane Dorian strengthens to Category 4}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian intensifies into a Category 4 hurricane roughly 400&nbsp;mi (645&nbsp;km) east of the northwestern [[Bahamas]] and 575&nbsp;mi (925&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author1=John Cangialosi|author2=Andrew S. Latto|title=Hurricane Dorian Tropical Cyclone Update|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.update.08310027.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=August 31, 2019|accessdate=September 19, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n=== September ===\n[[File:Dorian 2019-09-01 1500Z.jpg|thumb|Dorian 2019-09-01 1500Z|[[Hurricane Dorian]] near peak intensity making landfall the Great Abaco on September 1.]]\n'''September&nbsp;1'''\n* 12:00&nbsp;UTC (8:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|26.5|-76.5|name=Hurricane Dorian strengthens to Category 5}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian intensifies into a Category 5 hurricane roughly 35&nbsp;mi (55&nbsp;km) east of [[Abaco Islands|Great Abaco]] and 225&nbsp;mi (360&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Lixion Avila|title=Hurricane Dorian Intermediate Advisory Number 32A|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public_a.032.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=September 1, 2019|accessdate=September 19, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n*18:00&nbsp;UTC (2:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|26.5|-77.1|name=Hurricane Dorian makes landfall on Great Abaco}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian makes landfall on [[Abaco Islands|Great Abaco]] roughly 185&nbsp;mi (295&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Lixion Avila|title=Hurricane Dorian Intermediate Advisory Number 33A|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public_a.033.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=September 1, 2019|accessdate=September 19, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''September&nbsp;2'''\n* 03:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] September&nbsp;1) at {{Coord|26.6|-77.9|name=Hurricane Dorian makes landfall on Grand Bahama}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian makes landfall on [[Grand Bahama]] roughly 55&nbsp;mi (90&nbsp;km) east of [[Freeport, Bahamas]] and 135&nbsp;mi (220&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=John Cangialosi|title=Hurricane Dorian Advisory Number 35|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public.035.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=September 2, 2019|accessdate=December 1, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|26.8|-78.3|name=Hurricane Dorian weakens to Category 4}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian weakens into a Category 4 hurricane roughly 30&nbsp;mi (50&nbsp;km) northeast of [[Freeport, Bahamas]] and 110&nbsp;mi (180&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Daniel Brown|title=Hurricane Dorian Advisory Number 37|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.public.037.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=September 2, 2019|accessdate=December 1, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n\n'''September&nbsp;3'''\n* 5:00&nbsp;UTC (1:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]) at {{Coord|26.8|-78.4|name=Hurricane Dorian weakens to Category 3}}&nbsp;\u2013 Hurricane Dorian weakens into a Category 3 hurricane roughly 25&nbsp;mi (40&nbsp;km) northeast of [[Freeport, Bahamas]] and 105&nbsp;mi (170&nbsp;km) east of [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite report|author=Robbie Berg|title=Hurricane Dorian Tropical Cyclone Update|url=https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/archive/2019/al05/al052019.update.09030455.shtml?|publisher=National Hurricane Center|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=December 1, 2019|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>\n* 15:00&nbsp;UTC (11:00&nbsp;a.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|E