ite_project_a_soaring_success_1_773028 |accessdate=4 August 2011 |newspaper=Evening Telegraph |date=9 November 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Pugh>{{cite web |last=Pugh |first=Elfyn |url=http://www.birdsofbritain.co.uk/features/red-kite2.asp |title=The Red Kite | publisher=Birds of Britain |accessdate=26 October 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Radio4>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00yz3t2 |title=BBC Radio 4, Debating Animals, Series 2, The Kestrel and Red Kite by Rod Liddle}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=rspb>RSPB Scotland, cited in [https://web.archive.org/web/20080928031357/http://news.scotsman.com/latest-scottish-news/Red-Kite-numbers-soar-to.4492268.jp The Scotsman], Monday 15 September 2008</ref>\n\n<ref name=rspb2>{{cite web |url=http://www.rspb.org.uk/wildlife/birdguide/name/r/redkite/distribution_population.aspx |title=Red kite: Distribution and population size |publisher=The RSPB |accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"RSPB conservation\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rspb.org.uk/wildlife/birdguide/name/r/redkite/conservation.aspx |title=Red Kite |work=RSPB Conservation |publisher=RSPB |accessdate=26 October 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Schreiber2000>{{cite journal |last1=Schreiber |first1=Arnd |last2=Stubbe |first2=Michael |last3=Stubbe |first3=Annegret |year=2000 |title=Red kite (''Milvus milvus'') and black kite (''M. migrans''): minute genetic interspecies distance of two raptors breeding in a mixed community (Falconiformes: Accipitridae) |journal=[[Biological Journal of the Linnean Society]] |volume=69 |issue=3 |pages=351\u2013365 |doi=10.1006/bijl.1999.0365|doi-access=free }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=WalesFavBird>{{cite web |title=The Welsh Kite Trust |url=http://www.welshkitetrust.org/ |accessdate=16 October 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105181926/http://welshkitetrust.org/ |archivedate=5 January 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=WelshKiteTrust>{{cite web |url=http://www.gigrin.co.uk/w/europe/europe.html |publisher=Welsh Kite Trust |title=Red Kites decline in Europe |accessdate=24 February 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131108015436/http://www.gigrin.co.uk/w/europe/europe.html |archivedate=8 November 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=WestmorlandGazette>{{cite news |url=http://www.thewestmorlandgazette.co.uk/news/8224578.Red_kites_to_make_a_Lake_District_return/ |title=Red kites to make a Lake District return |date=17 June 2010 |work=The Westmorland Gazette |publisher=Newsquest media group |accessdate=12 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=wildlifeextra>{{cite web |url=http://www.wildlifeextra.com/go/news/ireland-kites.html#cr |title=Red Kites fly again in Ireland |work=Wildlife Extra: News |publisher=Wildlife Extra |accessdate=26 October 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=whiteredkite>{{cite web |url=http://www.gigrin.co.uk/white_redkite.html |title=The White Kite |work=Gigrin Farm - The Red Kite feeding station |publisher=Gigrin Farm |accessdate=7 July 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090202133553/http://gigrin.co.uk/white_redkite.html |archivedate=2 February 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=yorkshireredkites>{{cite web |title=Red Kites and poisons |url=http://www.yorkshireredkites.net/index.php/important-info/red-kites-and-poisons |publisher=Yorkshire Red Kites |accessdate=12 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{ cite book | editor1-last=Cramp | editor1-first=Stanley | display-editors=etal | editor1-link=Stanley Cramp | year=1980 | chapter=''Milvus milvus'' Red Kite | title=Handbook of the Birds of Europe the Middle East and North Africa. The Birds of the Western Palearctic. Volume II: Hawks to Bustards | place=Oxford | publisher=Oxford University Press | isbn=978-0-19-857505-4 | pages=36\u201344 | ref=harv }}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{ cite journal | last1=Carter | first1=Ian | last2=Grice | first2=Phil | year=2000 | title=Studies of re-established Red Kites in England | journal=British Birds | volume=93 | issue= | pages=304\u2013322 | url=https://biodive