nze</nowiki>]\n* {{InternetBirdCollection|red-kite-milvus-milvus}}\n* {{VIREO|red+kite}}\n* {{IUCN_Map|22695072|Milvus milvus}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q156250}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:kite, red}}\n[[Category:Kites (birds)|red kite]]\n[[Category:Falconry]]\n[[Category:Milvus|red kite]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1758]]\n[[Category:Birds of prey of Africa]]\n[[Category:Birds of Cape Verde]]\n[[Category:Birds of Europe]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Carl Linnaeus|red kite]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toPalestine(link changed toPalestine (region)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_kite"}
{"title_page": "Pablo Rosario", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n | name           = Pablo Rosario\n | image          = \n | caption        = \n | fullname       = Pablo Paulino Rosario\n | birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1997|1|7|df=yes}}\n | birth_place    = [[Amsterdam]], Netherlands\n | currentclub    = [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]]\n | clubnumber     = 18\n | height         = 1.88 m\n | position       = [[Midfielder]]\n | youthyears1    = 2007&ndash;2008\n | youthclubs1    = [[AVV Swift]]\n | youthyears2    = 2008\n | youthclubs2    = [[Feyenoord]]\n | youthyears3    = 2008&ndash;2010\n | youthclubs3    = [[AFC DWS|DWS]]\n | youthyears4    = 2010&ndash;2014\n | youthclubs4    = [[Ajax Youth Academy|Ajax]]\n | youthyears5    = 2014&ndash;2015\n | youthclubs5    = [[Almere City FC|Almere City]]\n | years1         = 2015\u20132016\n | clubs1         = [[Almere City FC|Almere City]]\n | caps1          = 34\n | goals1         = 3\n | years2         = 2016\u2013\n | clubs2         = [[Jong PSV]]\n | caps2          = 43\n | goals2         = 7\n | years3         = 2017\u2013\n | clubs3         = [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]]\n | caps3          = 54\n | goals3         = 2\n | nationalyears1 = 2013\n | nationalteam1  = Netherlands U16\n | nationalcaps1  = 3\n | nationalgoals1 = 0\n | nationalyears2 = 2015\u2013\n | nationalteam2  = [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U19]]\n | nationalcaps2  = 2\n | nationalgoals2 = 0\n | nationalyears3 = 2018\u2013\n | nationalteam3  = [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]\n | nationalcaps3  = 1\n | nationalgoals3 = 0\n | club-update    = 9 July 2018\n | ntupdate       = (14:27, 23 March 2016 (UTC))\n}}\n\n'''Pablo Paulino Rosario''' (born 7 January 1997) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] of [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]] descent who plays for [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] and the [[Netherlands national football team]] as a [[midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nRosario began his football career in the youth ranks of [[AVV Swift]], followed by a brief stint with [[Feyenoord]], before joining his local club [[AFC DWS]]. In 2012 Dutch broadcasting company [[Humanistische Omroep|HUMAN]] released the documentary film [[The Price of Heaven]] which follows Rosario from the period in which he captained the D1 squad of DWS.<ref>[http://www.npo.nl/human-doc/07-06-2012/VPWON_1177467 De Prijs van de Hemel] NPO Gemist, 7 June 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.jupilerleague.nl/nieuws/1568 Uitgelicht: Pablo Rosario], [[Eerste Divisie|Jupiler League]], 4 November 2015</ref>\n\nHaving been sensationalized as the next [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]] by the media, Rosario is confronted with the choice of joining the youth academies of either [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[Feyenoord]] or [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], the [[Big Three (Netherlands)|top three]] clubs in the country. Rosario eventually decides for Ajax and in 2010 he joined the B2 squad (under-16) under coach [[Orlando Trustfull]].<ref>[http://www.volkskrant.nl/archief/voetbaltalent-vindt-weg-omhoog~a3256271/ Voetbaltalent vindt weg omhoog] De Volkskrant, 16 mei 2012</ref>\n\n===Almere City===\nIn 2014 Rosario transferred to Ajax's [[List of AFC Ajax affiliated clubs|partner club]] [[Almere City FC]]. On 7 August 2015 he made his debut for the first team in the [[Eerste Divisie]], the 2nd tier of professional football in the Netherlands, in a 3\u20133 draw at home against [[VVV-Venlo]]. He was subbed on by head coach [[Maarten Stekelenburg (footballer, born 1972)|Maarten Stekelenburg]] in the 59th minute for [[Soufyan Ahannach]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/08/07/netherlands/eerste-divisie/fc-omniworld/vvv-venlo/2039561/ Wedstrijdverslag Almere City FC - VVV-Venlo] bij Soccerway</ref>\n\n===PSV Eindhoven===\nOn 25 July 2016, Pablo Rosario signed a four-year deal for Dutch club [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/rosario-joins-psv-from-almere-city-fc.htm|title=Rosario joins PSV from Almere City FC|website=PSV.nl|access-date=25 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nRosario made his international debut playing for the Netherlands under-16 side in a friendly match against Austria U-16 on 9 February 2013. On 12 November 2015, he made his debut for the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U19]] in a [[2016 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification]] match against [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] which ended in a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/20/564695a9-304f9524-202939|title=Speler: Pablo Rosario|publisher=OnsOranje|accessdate=2016-03-22}}</ref>\n\nRosario earned his first full international call up when [[Ronald Koeman]] named him in the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] squad in October 2018.<ref>{{cite web \n|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/koeman-happy-with-emerging-netherlands-talents/\n|title=Koeman happy with emerging Netherlands talents\n|publisher=football-oranje.com\n|date=9 October 2018 |accessdate=11 October 2018}}</ref> He made his international debut in a friendly against Belgium on the 16th of October, coming on as a half-time substitute.\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|1 July 2019.}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Pablo Rosario |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/pablo-rosario/ |website=worldfootball.net |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Soccerway|408534|accessdate=17 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<sup>1</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>2</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|[[Almere City FC|Almere City]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Eerste Divisie|2015\u201316]]\n|[[Eerste Divisie]]\n|34||3||2||0||\