6]], [[2012 United States Senate election in Vermont|2012]], [[2018 United States Senate election in Vermont|2018]]}}\n{{s-inc|recent}}\n{{US Senator succession box\n| state = Vermont\n| class = 1\n| before = [[Jim Jeffords]]\n| start = January 3, 2007\n| alongside = [[Patrick Leahy]]\n}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Patty Murray]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[United States Senate Committee on Veterans' Affairs|U.S. Senate Veterans' Affairs Committee]]|years=2013\u20132015}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Johnny Isakson]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Jeff Sessions]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Ranking Member of the [[United States Senate Committee on the Budget|U.S. Senate Budget Committee]]|years=2015\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Amy Klobuchar]]|as=Chair of the Senate Democratic Steering and Outreach Committee}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[United States Senate Democratic Steering and Outreach Committee|U.S. Senate Democratic Outreach Committee]]|years=2017\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ben Cardin]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Current [[Seniority in the United States Senate|Seniority in the U.S. Senate]]|years=28th}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Sherrod Brown]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles related to Bernie Sanders\n|list1=\n{{VT-FedRep}}\n{{Current U.S. Senators}}\n{{USSenChairs}}\n{{US Senate leaders current}}\n{{USSenVT}}\n{{SenVACommitteeChairmen}}\n{{Third Party US Senators}}\n{{Civil rights movement}}\n{{2016 United States presidential election}}\n{{Mayor of Burlington, Vermont}}\n{{Patriot Act}}\n{{USCongRep-start|congresses=102nd\u2013116th [[United States Congress]]es|state=[[Vermont]]}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/102}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/103}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/104}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/105}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/106}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/107}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/108}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/109}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/110}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/111}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/112}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/113}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/114}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/115}}\n{{USCongRep/VT/116}}\n{{USCongRep-end}}}}\n{{Portal bar